Both outputs are written and `transcript.json` validates against the schema (25 iterations, 27 hypotheses, 26 analyses).

## Key findings

- **Targeted-therapy triad (dominant signal):** `feature_014 × feature_027 × feature_035` three-way interaction, p=1.4e-29. Among the 8 cells of the 2×2×2 table, 7 have response rate ~16-17% baseline; the dual-biomarker-positive (`feature_014=1 & feature_027=1`) patients who receive `feature_035` have 62.1% response (n=427) — a +46 pp absolute increase. Within-subgroup adjusted OR = 8.85 (p=2.2e-91).
- **Independent prognostic markers:** `feature_011` (OR 0.96/unit, p<1e-30), `feature_006` (p<1e-19), `feature_063`, `feature_092` (negative); `feature_099` (positive). Robust to subgroup exclusion.
- **No age effect:** `feature_078` (range 18-92, presumed age) is flat (p=0.83).
- **No bias signals:** Univariate race effect (p=9.6e-3) attenuates to non-significance after clinical adjustment. No statistically significant disparities in `feature_035` receipt or efficacy across race or insurance.
- **Secondary interaction:** `feature_093 × feature_121` (adjusted p=3e-3) — much smaller magnitude.
